  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Full 13-factor assessment: all factors are either assessed with documented achieved and required levels, or scoped-out with rationale. Decision: Not accepted — the Model Form factor achieves Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 4, representing a critical shortfall that cannot be offset at MRL 5 for a Class III device.",
