      "rationale": "Use error is scoped out for this COU because the CFD model is executed exclusively by trained computational engineers following a documented simulation protocol with mandatory peer review of all setup parameters. The operating procedure includes a pre-run checklist that eliminates the class of analyst-induced input errors that this factor targets. At MRL 5, scoping-out is justified only because the procedural controls are formally documented and auditable; this scoping decision is recorded in the V&V plan revision 3.1."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/model-form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/model-form-cou2",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — hemolysis constitutive law",
        "description": "The hemolysis constitutive model must be validated against at least three independent experimental datasets spanning the shear-stress and exposure-time space of the COU operating envelope. Prediction error for NIH must be within ±20% across all validation datasets. Sensitivity of NIH predictions to power-law exponent uncertainty must be quantified."
      },
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model achieves Gradation 2: it has been validated against a single experimental dataset (the FDA pump benchmark) within the COU operating range, but cross-validation against independent datasets (e.g. cone-and-plate viscometer data, Bludszuweit shear history data) has not been performed. The power-law exponents (C=3.62e-5, alpha=2.416, beta=0.785) are taken from the original 1990 calibration and have not been recalibrated against modern red blood cell damage data. Sensitivity analysis shows NIH predictions vary by a factor of 2.3 across the plausible range of published exponent values, which far exceeds the ±20% acceptance threshold. This critical shortfall in model form credibility is the primary basis for the Not Accepted decision."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
