        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria",
        "description": "All uncertain model inputs (fluid viscosity, pump geometry tolerances, inlet turbulence intensity) must have documented probability distributions derived from measurement data. Monte Carlo propagation must use at least 500 samples."
      },
      "rationale": "Probability distributions for all 8 uncertain inputs were derived from experimental calibration data. Monte Carlo UQ used 1000 samples. Sensitivity indices (Sobol first-order) were computed for each input. Fluid viscosity and rotational speed are the dominant uncertainty contributors (combined 74% of output variance). Model inputs meet required level."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/test-samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Test samples is scoped out because the validation experiments used a fluid analog (glycerol-water solution) rather than human blood, and the hemolysis measurement protocol relies on spectrophotometric plasma-free hemoglobin assay rather than direct red blood cell counting. The factor as defined in ASME V&V 40 pertains to biological sample variability in device testing; since no human or animal blood was used in the FDA pump benchmark experiments, the factor is not applicable to this validation dataset. This scoping decision is consistent with FDA guidance on the use of blood analogs in CFD hemolysis V&V."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/equivalency-input-parameters",
