        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Simulation input parameters must be demonstrably equivalent to the physical test conditions. Any discrepancies in geometry, fluid properties, or boundary conditions must be quantified and their effect on NIH bounded."
      },
      "rationale": "Equivalency was assessed for geometry (pump CAD vs. manufactured part: maximum deviation 0.08 mm, effect on NIH < 1.5%), fluid viscosity (matched to within 0.3 mPa·s), and boundary conditions (inlet velocity profile reconstructed from PIV measurements). All discrepancies are within documented tolerance bands. Equivalency of input parameters meets required level."
    }
